  "notes": [
    "Many fields exist in both legacy and new versions (e.g., birthDate/dateOfBirth, nationality/nationalityArray)",
    "The nationality system uses both cached fields and a relational PersonNationality table for flexibility",
    "Profession fields support both single enum value and array of values",
    "Verification has multiple levels of granularity (verificationLevel, personVerificationLevel, isVerified)",
    "Social media fields are comprehensive but may be incomplete for many persons",
    "Statistics fields (statementCount, caseCount, etc.) are maintained as denormalized counters",
    "Many fields are nullable to accommodate incomplete data",
    "The schema supports extensive political, legal, and controversy tracking"
